<p>About time!</p>
<p>Nitpicking:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Longyan, PROC</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If you were going for 'People's Republic of China', it's usually 'PRC'. I don't think 'PROC' was ever in use.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Traditional Chinese</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Longyan is in Mainland China (i.e. PRC), which uses Simplified Chinese. The only way Longyan would be using Tradition character is if you were dating this back to before the establishment of the PRC.</p>
<p>Ergo, changing to 'Simplified Chinese' will solve it.</p>

