			<div class="content" id="post-content-3632683">
									

<p>I don't see the style or tone of The Factory on this hub, nor get any actual feeling about them; the fact that the entire first tab is just descriptions about it from other groups makes it much less special. It's a problem I have with the group in general; I don't feel anything about them, I don't feel their style or what makes them stand out to me, and that's reflected in just making the entire first tab about them via other groups, rather than about them from, well, about them.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Of note is that the main page has several GOI formats that explain the nature of the Factory in multiple contradictory ways. This was a conscious decision by myself as the Factory has no real universally agreed upon interpretation, and so each of these formats is representative of a different headcanon that I was able to get summarized for me.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yes, this is right; but then again, so is (of the groups with hubs): AWCY?, Black Queen, Chaos Insurgency, CotBG, GOC, Nobody, Oneiroi, and Serpent's Hand, yet their hubs reflect a style and essence of the group that captures who/what they are <em>by them</em>, even if it's done in a singular interpretation. This doesn't do that, so it's an extremely unimpressive hub.</p>

							</div>

								
					
