														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3639801">
									

<p>I agree with this sentiment 100%. I like the Factory as a mysterious, surreal, grotesque entity, a more down-to-earth version of Wondertainment, with the amorality of MC&amp;D and the vagueness of Nobody. It should be cogs, rust, blood-stains and chains, dressed up in a thin veneer of rampant capitalism. This GOI format is good, in as much as it could exist in-universe, but I'd much prefer a little more variety. If the Factory is, in fact, &quot;everything you never knew you wanted, and more&quot;, I feel a wider range of formats, interpretations, and documents would go down much better. But hey, that's just me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
