				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/swashbuckle" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2976525); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2976525&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251162" alt="Swashbuckle" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2976525)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/swashbuckle" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2976525); return false;" >Swashbuckle</a></span> <span class="odate time_1546118357 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Dec 2018 21:19</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4102574">
									

<p>So not only is the Factory much older than I originally thought, but it's run by the personifications of its businesses? This paints them so much more in an eldritch, cosmic horror light than I could've ever imagined. It makes me wonder if the Factory is really all about profit, or if it's for something else inconceivable to human beings, only to the Robber Barons themselves. I mean, a desire for profit only goes so far when it seems like you can basically produce anything in mass quantities, and I'd imagine that such entities would be at this point unimaginably powerful and wealthy. Entertainment, maybe? The satisfaction of seeing so many human souls being crushed and tortured under the ruthless Gilded Age style work environments they create? It's interesting to think about.</p>

							</div>

								
					
